Note: Only auto attacks can critically strike, but Cramorant has 0% base Critical-Hit rate at all levels. At level 9, Cramorant gains 12.5% spell vamp (restores HP when dealing Special Attack damage).

Gulp Missile

Passive Ability

This Pokémon can catch some form of prey in their mouth when entering Whirlpool, Surf, or Dive. When receiving damage, counterattacks by spitting the prey in their mouth at an opposing Pokémon, damaging them and bouncing to 1 other opposing Pokémon nearby.

When above 50% max HP, catches Arrokuda as prey, which also decrease opposing Pokémon's Defense by 20% and Sp. Def by 5% for 3s. When below 50% max HP, instead catches Pikachu as prey, which decrease opposing Pokémon's movement speed by 50% and attack speed by 10% for 1s.

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack with every fourth attack, catching some form of prey. This boosted attack spits prey at an opposing Pokémon, damaging them and bouncing to 1 other opposing Pokémon nearby.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

76% SpA + 16 x (Level - 1) + 290

Whirlpool

Move 1

5.00s Area

The user creates a whirlpool at a designated location, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect over 1.8s (up to 10 times). The area of effect shrinks in size over the duration; opposing Pokémon standing at the outer edge of the whirlpool are hit only up to 3 times. The movement speed of opposing Pokémon in the area of effect is decreased by 50% for 0.2s when hit.

The user can enter the whirlpool to catch prey for Gulp Missile (up to 2 times).

24% SpA + 5 x (Level - 1) + 100

27% SpA + 6 x (Level - 1) + 110

30% SpA + 7 x (Level - 1) + 120

Whirlpool Upgrade Choices

Surf

7.50s Ranged

The user sends a wave in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon in the wave. The wave reaches its maximum distance after 0.8s, then returns to its starting point at the same speed, damaging opposing Pokémon and pulling them with the returning wave, stunning them for 0.4s during the pull.

The user catches prey with the first wave, and can enter the returning wave to catch more prey for Gulp Missile.

75% SpA + 9 x (Level - 1) + 390

112.5% SpA + 14 x (Level - 1) + 585

The first wave decreases the movement speed of opposing Pokémon hit by 40% for 3s.

Dive

6.00s Dash

The user becomes unstoppable for 0.5s as they change the designated location into a puddle then dive to the puddle, damaging opposing Pokémon and shoving them for 0.5s when the user emerges from the puddle. The next boosted attack within 5s deals additional damage; boosted attacks after 5s have passed become regular boosted attacks. A maximum of 3 uses can be kept in reserve for this move, and there is a 2s cooldown between uses.

The user catches prey for Gulp Missile as they emerge from the puddle.

45% SpA + 9 x (Level - 1) + 180

38% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 145

Increases the damage of the dive.

50% SpA + 10 x (Level - 1) + 210

Feather Dance

Move 2

8.00s Debuff

The user throws a circle of feathers at the designated area, decreasing the Attack of opposing Pokémon in the area of effect by 30% and their movement speed by 20% for 4s.

Feather Dance Upgrade Choices

Hurricane

7.50s Hindrance

The user creates a fierce wind at the designated location. After 0.5s, a hurricane catches opposing Pokémon in the area of effect, damaging them and throwing them for 1s.

120% SpA + 11 x (Level - 1) + 620

Increases the user's movement speed by 20% for 3s.

Air Slash

8.00s Ranged

The user shoots out 5 blades of air in a cone in the designated direction, damaging the first opposing Pokémon hit with each blade. The user also hops backward to create distance. This move's cooldown is reduced by 0.5s for each blade that hits (up to 2.5s).

35% SpA + 6 x (Level - 1) + 150

Restores the user's HP for each blade of air that hits an opposing Pokémon.

30% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 40

Gatling Gulp Missile

Unite Move

123s 110000 Area

Unlocks at level 9

The user becomes unstoppable for up to 6.5s and catches a series of prey to spit at the nearest Pokémon from the opposing team or wild Pokémon up to 10 times. The user cannot move or use moves while using Gatling Gulp Missile. The user can use this Unite Move again to cancel it early. The prey caught for each Gatling Gulp Missile attack depends on the user's current HP.

If a boosted attack is readied when this Unite Move is used, the user spits out this prey out first as a regular boosted attack before catching and spitting out up to 10 Gatling Gulp Missile prey.

85% SpA + 8 x (Level - 1) + 330

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Max HP Shield granted at the start of the Move, 30% Movement Speed granted at the end of the turret
